Two killed and others injured in bomb attack in Songkhla Friday morning
At least two were killed and seven others injured in a bomb attack at a company in Songkhla on Friday morning.
The explosion took place in front of Pitanpanich company in Nathawee district at 7am. The district is a border district with Pattani province which is hit by attacks on daily basis.
Police said the blast took place a day after a group of insurgents working in the area reported themselves to authorities.